# Fish Shell Configuration Guidelines

## Configuration Structure
```
fish/
├── config.fish          # Main configuration
├── functions/           # Custom functions
├── completions/         # Custom completions
└── conf.d/             # Configuration snippets
```

## Core Principles
- Use abbr for frequently used commands
- Create functions for complex operations
- Maintain clean, readable syntax
- Optimize for development workflow

## Development-Focused Configurations
- Git shortcuts and aliases
- Node.js/npm workflow enhancements
- Docker command shortcuts
- Project navigation functions

## System Integration
- Integration with window manager shortcuts
- Terminal-specific optimizations
- File manager integration
- Clipboard utilities

## Performance Considerations
- Fast prompt rendering
- Efficient path handling
- Minimal startup time
- Lazy loading of heavy functions

## Example Function Structure
```fish
function dev_setup --description "Setup development environment"
    # Implementation
end
```

## Abbreviations Categories
- Git operations: `ga`, `gc`, `gp`, `gl`
- System operations: `ll`, `la`, `..`, `...`
- Development: `nr`, `ni`, `nrd`
- Navigation: `cdp` (cd to projects), `cdc` (cd to configs)
